Job Description
Employer: John Hancock Life Insurance Company (USA)
Job Site : 200 Berkeley Street, Boston, MA 02116
Job Title: Data Scientist
Job Duties:
Apply statistical methods, machine learning algorithms and predictive models to solve business problems across the business and work closely with Analytics and Business teams;
Develop supervised machine learning models including multinomial logistic regression and poisson regression;
Support vector machines, neural networks, ensemble techniques such as Gradient Boosting Machine, Random Forest regularization techniques such as Lasso/Ridge to make predictions from data to solve business problems;
Develop unsupervised machine learning models such as k-means clustering and hierarchical clustering to identify patterns and draw inferences from data;
Utilize text mining and natural language processing techniques to identify patterns in text data and provide actionable insights to business units;
Manipulate Big Data storage utilizing Amazon Web Services (AWS), Apache Hadoop, Hive, Apache Mahoot and emerging Big Data technology;
Utilize big data technology tools such as SQL, HiveQL, PySparkd and Hadoop to retrieve large sized data from Enterprise Data Lake to perform data analysis;
Perform data manipulation on data stored in Enterprise Data Lake;
Deliver data from internal and external sources;
Communicate with product owners from Big Data Team to procure in-house and third-party data from Enterprise Data Lake using tools such as SAS, PySpark, Hadoop, HiveQL and SQL;
Create dashboards using Tableau, R-Shiny and QlikView to present analysis findings;
Utilize outlier detection techniques such as Median Absolute Deviation and Box-Cox Transformation to detect and treat outliers (data deviations);
Benchmark model performance using techniques such as Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC), Curve/Accuracy, Precision and Recall statistics, R-Squared, Mean Squared Error, Akaike Information Criteria, and Bayesian Information Criteria to select data models for regression models;
Leverage techniques such as P-value, Variation Inflation Factor (VIF) score, Z- score, and F-Statistic to ensure variables used in models are statistically significant;
Use SQL to query in-house data to prepare for analysis and modeling purposes;
Develop SQL code to store cleaned data in Microsoft Azure Server databases;
Leverage visualization tools such as Kibana, Tableau, R-Shiny, and QLikView to effectively communicate analysis results to business stakeholders;
Participate in monthly Advanced Analytics best practices meetings and Annual Advanced Analytics Conference to learn about new findings, use cases, and analysis techniques used during projects by fellow Data Scientists.
Minimum Requirements:
Master’s degree or foreign equivalent in Industrial Engineering, Applied Statistics, Operations Research or related field and 2 years of experience in a data science role. Experience must include:
Two (2) years of experience with programming languages such as R, Python, or shell scripting;
Two (2) years of experience with scripting languages such as SAS or SQL for querying underlying data;
Two (2) years of experience with dashboarding tools such as Tableau, Qlikview or Kibana;
Two (2) years of experience with programming languages and underlying libraries including: R, Shiny, Python, Flask, NetworkX; or ElasticSearch for data visualization;
Two (2) years of experience using programming languages such as R and Python for model building; and SQL for data querying/engineering;
Two (2) years of experience of using cloud based data servers such as Azure, AWS or Hadoop;
Two (2) years of experience using Github, Gitlab or SVM for code version control, code deployment into production and tracking outputs;
Experience may be gained concurrently.
